                <article data-uuid="c83d46fa1e334bed82adf46a0b406baa">
                    <h3 class="mod" data-uuid="479370df69794bb585cf32dbb13bd915">Reconstruction, 1860–1880
                    </h3>
                    <p class="mod" data-uuid="5d793cbe9ac54001a9564fe41a0a4950">The differences that caused the Civil War, and
                        the bitterness that followed, created further divisions in American politics and society
                        after the war ended. A reunified United States began to take a larger
                        role in the world. The new nations of Italy and Germany changed the balance of
                        power in Europe, and in Asia, Japan became more powerful.<br />
                    </p>
